&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;**THIS VACANCY IS ONLY OPEN TO EMPLOYEES OF WORCESTERSHIRE ACUTE HOSPITALS NHS TRUST**&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Breast Imaging Clerk/Receptionist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking to recruit a Breast Imaging Clerk/Receptionist to work as part of the specialist Breast Imaging team based at the Princess of Wales Community Hospital, Bromsgrove, part of Worcestershire Acute NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is fundamental to provide support to the administrative and clerical function of the screening and symptomatic breast imaging service that is delivered within national guidelines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide the breast screening service as part of the NHS Breast Screening Programme to an eligible population of approximately 210,000 within the counties of Herefordshire and Worcestershire and a symptomatic breast service across multiple sites within Worcestershire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be required to work as part of the multi-disciplinary team, will possess excellent administration skills, a high level of accuracy, flexibility,the ability to work from other sites as necessary and will demonstrate a commitment to Worcestershire Acute Hospitals NHS Trust to provide a high quality breast imaging service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal enquires please contact – Helen Handy, Breast Imaging Admin Manager on:  01527 488055 or ext 58487 or email helen.handy1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
